<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102959735060831></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102959735060831><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=14379&mid=102959735060831>RE: Price</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=14379&mid=102959735060831#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=137802><span id= >Leenyn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 17th 11:27 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I only partially agree with this philosophy, and here is why.....<br><br>While I concede that it costs a lot to take up a skill, I don't believe it to be fair to charge your skill up cost plus the item, in one sale.<br><br>For a perfect example on this, I smith a bit, with a skill of 109.&nbsp;&nbsp;When jaggedpine came out and the non-stick frying pans, I went and made one.  Cost me about a 2p to make it.  So I figured I would make a couple extra and sell them in the bazaar. made 15 more, for a total cost to me of like 30pp.<br>Went to the bazaar, and saw the lowest priced one was 65pp. So does this mean that a roughly four thousand percent markup is justifiable?  No, it was from people who were trying to justify their overhead, as you say.<br>I sold my first two pans at 15pp within 3 minutes, and marked them down to 10pp.  Sold two more within a minute, and marked them down to 5pp and sold out the rest within 5 minutes.<br>went back, made 40 more (2 failures) and sold them within a day at 5pp each. The people selling for 65pp still had all of theirs.....<br><br>My point is, price gouging is ridiculous and greedy.  There may be a bunch of losers out there that took advantage of exploits and *have a buttload of plat* that can afford gougers....but average folks can't afford good things, because the trader is trying to make the customer pay for the traders own incompetence in making an item. <br><br>Sure, I failed on making items.  That was MY responsibility to pay, because I chose to take up that skill.<br>Heh heh.  So on my server...I will undercut gougers every time I can....=)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
